			<div class="content" id="post-content-4862019">
									

<blockquote>
<p>So what makes the foundation once you strip away the O5 council and the researchers?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In addition to the Council and Research/Development, the Foundation also has a lot of administrative and military infrastructure. The Council is generally understand as kinds of &quot;eyes in the sky&quot;, but in their absence each site would exercise regional oversight and probably have the manpower to maintain the status quo. Big picture stuff, like making some world-saving weapon or another, requires some level of comprehensive knowledge of the anomalous and research/development.</p>
<p>If you were to ask me &quot;What is the Foundation's essense?&quot; I'd probably respond that it's their particular dogma. Research and containment, essentially. The Council, researchers, and nearly everything else is built on maintaining a status quo.</p>

